My rule of thumb is that a human body plan adds a bit of weight, to account for our long limbs and the whole walking upright thing. Franky is also at the upper range for her species, though Stephen doesn't have the frame of reference to notice this. She's also both chubby and muscular, so that amounts to her being quite heavy. How heavy, I'm not sure. There's a bit of hyperbole in Stephen's descriptions, though she's definitely heavier than a regular, non-upright tigress. When I was looking up how big tigers get, my thought process was just "that plus a bit", so I quickly ended up with her height being twice that of a normal person because, frankly, it's just easier to keep in mind when writing stuff.

I originally started writing with Trump's Imperfect Item in mind, too. The big anthro in that is stated as being 400 kg or something.
